#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_packedscene.rst:19
msgid ""
"A simplified interface to a scene file. Provides access to operations and"
" checks that can be performed on the scene resource itself."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_packedscene.rst:21
msgid ""
"Can be used to save a node to a file. When saving, the node as well as "
"all the node it owns get saved (see ``owner`` property on :ref:`Node "
"<class_Node>`)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_packedscene.rst:23
msgid "**Note:** The node doesn't need to own itself."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_packedscene.rst:25
msgid ""
"**Example of saving a node with different owners:** The following example"
" creates 3 objects: ``Node2D`` (``node``), ``RigidBody2D`` (``rigid``) "
"and ``CollisionObject2D`` (``collision``). ``collision`` is a child of "
"``rigid`` which is a child of ``node``. Only ``rigid`` is owned by "
"``node`` and ``pack`` will therefore only save those two nodes, but not "
"``collision``."
msgstr ""

